<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[324,486,260,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agilis">
<emphasis box="[324,486,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Alpheus agilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously known from 
<collectingCountry box="[828,896,260,285]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Brazil</collectingCountry>
based on a single record from Atol das 
<taxonomicName box="[1367,1436,261,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Salmoneus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rocas">Rocas</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Anker" box="[158,363,295,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Anker, A., Hurt, C. &amp; Knowlton, N. (2009) Description of cryptic taxa within the Alpheus bouvieri A. Milne-Edwards, 1878 and A. hebes Kim and Abele, 1988 species complexes (Crustacea: Decapoda: Alpheidae). Zootaxa, 2153, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="2009">
Anker 
<emphasis box="[238,296,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[304,363,296,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Soledade &amp; Almeida 
<number box="[623,681,296,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2013.0">2013</number>
) and is here recorded for the first time from Trindade 
<collectingCountry box="[1302,1374,295,320]" name="Iceland" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Island</collectingCountry>
. This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Milne-Edwards, 1878" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1878" box="[493,930,332,357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bouvieri">
<emphasis box="[493,623,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A. bouvieri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards" box="[637,930,332,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1878) Description de quelques especes nouvelles de crustaces provenant du voyage aux iles du Cap Vert de MM. Bouvier et Cessac. Bulletin de la Societe Philomatique de Paris, Serie 7, 2, 225 - 232." type="journal article" year="1878">
A. Milne-Edwards, 
<number box="[871,930,332,356]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1878.0">1878</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, an amphi-Atlantic snapping shrimp fairly common on the continental coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[583,651,367,392]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Soledade &amp; Almeida 
<number box="[925,983,368,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2013.0">2013</number>
) and in 
<collectingCountry box="[1086,1203,367,392]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Ascension</collectingCountry>
<collectingCountry box="[1213,1281,367,392]" name="Iceland" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Island</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Manning" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Manning, R. B. &amp; Chace, F. A. Jr. (1990) Decapod and stomatopod Crustacea from Ascension Island, South Atlantic Ocean. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 503, i - v, 1 - 91. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.503" type="journal article" year="1990">
Manning &amp; Chace 
<number box="[230,289,404,428]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="De" box="[303,549,404,428]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="De Grave, S., Anker, A., Dworschak, P. C., Clark, P. F. &amp; Wirtz, P. (2014) An updated checklist of the marine Decapoda of Ascension Island, central Atlantic Ocean. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, CJO 2014, 1 - 12. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315414001295" type="journal article" year="2014">
<collectingCountry box="[303,336,405,428]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">De</collectingCountry>
Grave 
<emphasis box="[422,480,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[489,549,404,428]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but curiously not (yet?) found in the Trindade and Martin Vaz Archipelago. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,310,440,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agilis">
<emphasis box="[151,310,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Alpheus agilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated by 
<taxonomicName box="[545,669,440,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bouvieri">
<emphasis box="[545,669,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A. bouvieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most easily by the presence of a stout spiniform seta on the ischium of the third and fourth pereiopods, which is absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[750,874,476,500]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bouvieri">
<emphasis box="[750,874,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A. bouvieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
